{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Normalizes active take of selected audio items to a user defineable LUFS max momentary value (sets Item take volume).\line This version of the script doesn't give a user prompt to set the target value (for use in custom actions),\line but instead uses the target value set in the related script "nofish_Set normalize loudness to X LUFS max momentary target vaulue.lua"\line Note: 'Momentary loudness' uses a time window of 0.4 sec. for analysis, so items shorter than this can't be analyzed / normalized correctly.\line In the script's USER CONFIG AREA can be set if info / progress should be displayed in the console.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Requires REAPER v5.21 / SWS v2.9.6 or above\par}
}

